The distribution of 70 new constituencies as outlined in the BBI bill is once again emerging as a thorny issue even as the joint legal affairs committee of the two houses of parliament prepares to submit their report. Nairobi senator Johnson Sakaja and his Murang&rsquo;a counterpart Irungu Kang&rsquo;ata have voiced dissenting opinion on whether or not increasing or decreasing electoral boundaries should be left to the Independent Electoral and Boundaries Commission.&nbsp;&nbsp;